trans-unit.source: Exception occurs in PCA module if number of dimensions to reduce to is equal to number of feature columns in input dataset, containing at least one sparse feature column.
trans-unit.target: Exception occurs in PCA module if number of dimensions to reduce to is equal to number of feature columns in input dataset, containing at least one sparse feature column.

trans-unit.source: This error is produced if the following conditions are met: (a) the input dataset has at least one sparse column and (b) the final number of dimensions requested is the same as the number of input dimensions.
trans-unit.target: This error is produced if the following conditions are met: (a) the input dataset has at least one sparse column and (b) the final number of dimensions requested is the same as the number of input dimensions.

trans-unit.source: Consider reducing the number of dimensions in the output to be fewer than the number of dimensions in the input.
trans-unit.target: Consider reducing the number of dimensions in the output to be fewer than the number of dimensions in the input.

trans-unit.source: This is typical in applications of PCA.
trans-unit.target: This is typical in applications of PCA.

trans-unit.source: For dataset containing sparse feature columns number of dimensions to reduce to should be less than number of feature columns.
trans-unit.target: For dataset containing sparse feature columns number of dimensions to reduce to should be less than number of feature columns.
